Linear Algorithm: Cross Correlation¶

{𝐹𝑡}⟶{𝑆𝑡+𝑘}{Ft}⟶{St+k}¶

Non-Linear Algorithm: Dynamic Time Wrapping¶

{𝐹𝑡}⟶{𝑆𝑔(𝑡)}{Ft}⟶{Sg(t)}¶

Rematch the time axis of two time series by 𝑔(𝑡)g(t), such that min{(𝑆𝑔(𝑡)−𝐹𝑡)2}min{(Sg(t)−Ft)2}¶

Quantification¶

Using the lead-lag relation given by DTW, ¶

When stock leads future, compute: ∑𝑠𝑖𝑔𝑛(𝑆𝑡−𝑆𝑡−𝑚)(𝐹𝑡+𝑛−𝐹𝑡)∑sign(St−St−m)(Ft+n−Ft)¶

When future leads stock, compute: ∑𝑠𝑖𝑔𝑛(𝐹𝑡−𝐹𝑡−𝑚)(𝑆𝑡+𝑛−𝑆𝑡)∑sign(Ft−Ft−m)(St+n−St)¶

date = '20190710'
future = 'IF1907'
stock = '000300.SH'

st = Table.read_table(date + '/' + stock + '_' + date + '_preprocessed_smooth.csv')
ft = Table.read_table(date + '/' + future + '_' + date + '_preprocessed_smooth.csv')
st = st.take(np.arange(0, st.num_rows, 10)) # 5秒1次
ft = ft.take(np.arange(0, ft.num_rows, 10))

st = Table().with_columns(
    'time', st.column('time'),
    'index', compute_increment(st.column('index'))
)
ft = Table().with_columns(
    'time', ft.column('time'),
    'index', compute_increment(ft.column('index'))
)
